## System Architecture Overview

The orchestrator is written in TypeScript and consists of several loosely‑coupled modules. While you will not run the TypeScript code directly in a chat environment, understanding the module responsibilities is essential for implementing the same logic manually.

| Module | Responsibility |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Core Orchestrator** | Greedy scheduler, dependency resolution, octopus merge, governance. |
| **Plan Generator** | Breaks high‑level goals into numbered steps with assigned agents and dependencies. |
| **Session Executor** | Manages Copilot CLI subprocesses (replaced by chat prompts in our adaptation). |
| **Verification Engine** | Parses transcripts and git history to confirm that promises were kept. |
| **Repair Agent** | Classifies failures and applies corrective strategies. |
| **Quality Gates** | Eight post‑merge checks that run on the final codebase. |
| **Cost Estimator** | Predicts premium request usage based on plan and historical failure rates. |

